               <msContents>
                  <summary> Renowned Safavid-era calligrapher <persName xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc"
                        >Sulṭān Muḥammad Khandān (fl. early 16th c.)</persName> completed this copy
                     of the <title>Dīvān</title> of Ḥāfiẓ (ca. 1315–1390) in <placeName
                        ref="http://vocab.getty.edu/page/tgn/7002243" key="place_7002243"
                        >Herat</placeName> in <date calendar="#Hijri-qamari" when="1530">937 AH
                        (1530 CE)</date>. This volume features most of the ghazal lyric poems set
                     within lavishly illuminated margins, although it omits quatrains typically
                     found in other copies. </summary>
